obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (28911)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent, application and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes `1. 5th July, 2017, vide notification No. G.S.R. 827(E), dated 5th July, 2017, see Gazette of India, Part II, s. 3.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00011_201630_1517807328179&sectionId=28911&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00011_201630_1517807328179
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the AntiHijacking Act, 2016.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India and, save as otherwise provided in this Act, it applies also to`
  line `any offence thereunder committed outside India by any person.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (28912)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00011_201630_1517807328179&sectionId=28912&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00011_201630_1517807328179
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,––`
  line
  line `(a) "Agency" means the National Investigation Agency constituted under section 3 of the`
  line `National Investigation Agency Act, 2008 (34 of 2008);`
  line
  line `(b) "aircraft" means any aircraft, whether or not registered in India, other than a military`
  line `aircraft or an aircraft used in customs or police service;`
  line
  line `(c) "aircraft registered in India" means an aircraft which is for the time being registered in`
  line India;
  line
  line `(d) "Convention country" means a country in which the Hague Convention is for the time`
  line `being in force;`
  line
  line `(e) "Hague Convention" means the Convention for the Suppression of Unlawful Seizure of`
  line `Aircraft signed at The Hague on the 16th day of December, 1970 and includes the Protocol`
  line `Supplementary to the Convention signed at Beijing on the 10th day of September, 2010;`
  line
  line `(f) "hostage" means a passenger or a crew member of an aircraft or any security personnel on`
  line `board the aircraft or a ground support staff involved in the maintenance of the aircraft, who is`
  line `unlawfully seized or detained without his consent, or with his consent obtained by fraud or duress,`
  line `by an individual or by a group of persons, during the transit of an aircraft or when it is stationed at`
  line `an airport, with an intention to secure any demand or fulfilment of any condition made by such`
  line `individual or such group of persons;`
  line
  line `(g) "military aircraft" means an aircraft of the naval, military, air force or any other armed`
  line `forces of any country and includes every aircraft commanded for the time being by a person in`
  line `any such force detailed for the purpose;`
  line
  line `(h) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(i) "security personnel" means security personnel deployed by the Central Government or`
  line `appointed by any agency authorised by that Government to ensure security of civil aviation`
  line `against acts of unlawful interference.`
  line
  line `Explanation.––for the purposes of this clause "acts of unlawful interference" means acts or`
  line `attempted acts to jeopardize the safety of civil aviation and air transport, including––`
  line
  line `(i) unlawful seizure of aircraft in flight;`
  line
  line `(ii) unlawful seizure of aircraft on the ground;`
  line
  line `(iii) hostage-taking on board aircraft or on aerodromes;`
  line
  line `(iv) forcible intrusion on board aircraft, at an aerodrome or on the premises on an aeronautical`
  line facility;
  line
  line `(v) introduction on board an aircraft or at an aerodrome, of a weapon, explosive or other`
  line `hazardous device, article or substances intended for criminal purposes;`
  line
  line `(vi) communication of false information with a view to jeopardize the safety of an aircraft in`
  line `flight or on the ground, of passengers, crew, ground personnel or the general public, at an`
  line `aerodrome or on the premises of a civil aviation facility.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (28913)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Hijacking.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00011_201630_1517807328179&sectionId=28913&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00011_201630_1517807328179
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever unlawfully and intentionally seizes or exercises control of an`
  line `aircraft in service by force or threat thereof, or by coercion, or by any other form of intimidation, or`
  line `by any technological means, commits the offence of hijacking.`
  line
  line `(2) A person shall also be deemed to have committed the offence of hijacking specified in`
  line `sub-section (1), if, such person--`
  line
  line `(a) makes a threat to commit such offence or unlawfully and intentionally causes any person`
  line `to receive such threat under circumstances which indicate that the threat is credible; or`
  line
  line `(b) attempts to commit or abets the commission of such offence; or`
  line
  line `(c) organises or directs others to commit such offence or the offence specified in clause (a) or`
  line `clause (b) above;`
  line
  line `(d) participates as an accomplice in such offence or the offence specified in clause (a) or`
  line `clause (b) above;`
  line
  line `(e) unlawfully and intentionally assists another person to evade investigation, prosecution or`
  line `punishment, knowing that such person has committed any such offence or the offence specified in`
  line `clause (a) or clause (b) or clause (c) or clause (d) above, or that such person is wanted for criminal`
  line `prosecution by law enforcement authorities for such an offence or has been sentenced for such an`
  line offence.
  line
  line `(3) A person also commits the offence of hijacking, when committed intentionally, whether or not`
  line `any of the offences specified in sub-section (1) or in clause (a) of sub-section (2) is actually`
  line `committed or attempted, either or both of the following:--`
  line
  line `(a) agreeing with one or more other persons to commit an offence specified in sub-section (1)`
  line `or in clause (a) of sub-section (2), involving an act undertaken by one of the participants in`
  line `furtherance of the agreement; or`
  line
  line `(b) contributing in any manner to the commission of an offence specified in sub-section (1) or`
  line `in clause (a) of sub-section (2) by a group of persons acting with a common purpose and such`
  line `contribution shall either--`
  line
  line `(i) be made with the aim of furthering the general criminal activity or purpose of the`
  line `group, where such activity or purpose involves the commission of such an offence; or`
  line
  line `(ii) be made in the knowledge of the intention of the group to commit such offence.`
  line
  line `(4) For the purposes of this Act, an aircraft shall be considered to be 'in service" from the`
  line `beginning of the pre-flight preparation of the aircraft by ground personnel or by the crew for a specific`
  line `flight until twenty-four hours after any landing and in the case of a forced landing, the flight shall be`
  line `deemed to continue until the competent authorities take over the responsibility for the aircraft and for`
  line `persons and property on board.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (28914)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Punishment for hijacking.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00011_201630_1517807328179&sectionId=28914&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00011_201630_1517807328179
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `Whoever commits the offence of hijacking shall be punished--`
  line
  line `(a) with death where such offence results in the death of a hostage or of a security personnel`
  line `or of any person not involved in the offence, as a direct consequence of the office of hijacking; or`
  line
  line `(b) with imprisonment for life which shall mean imprisonment for the remainder of that`
  line `person's natural life and with fine,`
  line
  line `and the movable and immovable property of such person shall`
  line `also be liable to be confiscated.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (28915)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Punishment for acts of violence connected with hijacking.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00011_201630_1517807328179&sectionId=28915&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00011_201630_1517807328179
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, being a person`
  line `committing the offence of hijacking of an aircraft, commits, in connection with such offence, any act`
  line `of violence against any passenger or member of the crew of such aircraft, shall be punished with the`
  line `same punishment with which he would have been punishable under any law for the time being in`
  line `force in India if such act had been committed in India.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (28916)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Conferment of powers of investigations, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00011_201630_1517807328179&sectionId=28916&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00011_201630_1517807328179
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of this Act, the Central`
  line `Government may, notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure,`
  line `1973 (2 of 1974), by notification, confer on any officer of the Central Government or any officer of`
  line `the Agency, powers of arrest, investigation and prosecution exercisable by a police officer under the`
  line `said Code.`
  line
  line `(2) All officers of police and all officers of Government are hereby required and empowered to`
  line `assist the officer of the Central Government referred to in sub-section (1) in the execution of the`
  line `provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (28917)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title Jurisdiction.
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00011_201630_1517807328179&sectionId=28917&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00011_201630_1517807328179
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (2), where an offence under section`
  line `3 or section 5 is committed outside India, the person committing such offence may be dealt with in`
  line `respect thereof as if such offence had been committed at any place within India at which he may be`
  line found.
  line
  line `(2) No Court shall take cognizance of an offence punishable under section 3 or section 5 which is`
  line `committed outside India unless,––`
  line
  line `(a) such offence is committed within the territory of India;`
  line
  line `(b) such offence is committed against or on board an aircraft registered in India;`
  line
  line `(c) such offence is committed on board and the aircraft in which the offence is committed`
  line `lands in India with the alleged offender still on board;`
  line
  line `(d) such offence is committed against or on board an aircraft which is for the time being`
  line `leased without crew to a lessee who has his principal place of business or where he has no such`
  line `place of business, his permanent residence is in India;`
  line
  line `(e) such offence is committed by or against a citizen of India;`
  line
  line `(f) such offence is committed by a stateless person whose habitual residence is in the territory`
  line `of India;`
  line
  line `(g) such offence is committed by the alleged offender who is present in India but not`
  line `extradited under section 11.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (28918)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Designated Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00011_201630_1517807328179&sectionId=28918&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00011_201630_1517807328179
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purpose of providing for speedy trial, the State Government`
  line `shall, with the concurrence of the Chief Justice of the High Court, by notification, specify a Court of`
  line `Sessions to be a Designated Court for such area or areas as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding the provisions of sub-section (1), the Special Court Constituted under`
  line `section 11 or, as the case may be, under section 22 of the National Investigation Agency`
  line `Act, 2008 (34 of 2008) shall be the Designated Court for the purposes of this Act in case where the`
  line `power of arrest, investigation and prosecution is exercised by the Agency under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 6.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), a`
  line `Designated Court shall, as far as practicable, hold the trial on a day-to-day basis.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (28919)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Offences triable by Designated Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00011_201630_1517807328179&sectionId=28919&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00011_201630_1517807328179
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code`
  line `of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974),--`
  line
  line `(a) all offences under this Act shall be triable by the Designated Court referred to in section 8.`
  line
  line `(b) where a person who is accused or suspected of the commission of an offence under this`
  line `Act is forwarded to the Magistrate under sub-section (2) or sub-section (2A) of section 167 of the`
  line `Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), such Magistrate may authorise detention of such`
  line `person in such custody, as he thinks fit, for a period not exceeding thirty days in the whole, where`
  line `such Magistrate is a Judicial Magistrate, and seven days in the whole, where such Magistrate is an`
  line `Executive Magistrate:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Magistrate may, if he considers that the detention of such person is not`
  line `required, ---`
  line
  line `(i) when such person is forwarded to him as aforesaid; or`
  line
  line `(ii) upon or at any time before the expiry of the period of detention authorised by him,`
  line
  line `he shall order such person to be forwarded to the Designated Court having jurisdiction;`
  line
  line `(c) the Designated Court may exercise, in relation to the person forwarded to it under clause (b),`
  line `the same power which a Magistrate having jurisdiction to try a case may exercise under section 167 of`
  line `the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), in relation to an accused person in such case who`
  line `has been forwarded to him under that section;`
  line
  line `(d) the Designated Court may, upon perusal of the report filled by the Agency or a complaint`
  line `made by an officer of the Central Government, or the State Government, as the case may be,`
  line `authorised in this behalf, take cognizance of the offence without the accused being committed to it for`
  line trial.
  line
  line `(2) When trying an offence under this Act, a Designated Court may also try an offence other than`
  line `an offence under this Act, which the accused may, under the Code of Criminal Procedure,`
  line `1973 (2 of 1974), be charged at the same trial.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (28920)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Application of Code to proceedings before Designated Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00011_201630_1517807328179&sectionId=28920&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00011_201630_1517807328179
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise`
  line `provided in this Act, the provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) shall apply`
  line `to the proceedings before a Designated Court and the person conducting a prosecution before a`
  line `Designated Court shall be deemed to be a Public Prosecutor.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (28921)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Provisions as to extradition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00011_201630_1517807328179&sectionId=28921&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00011_201630_1517807328179
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The offences under section 3 and section 5 shall be`
  line `deemed to have been included as extraditable offences and provided for in all the extradition treaties`
  line `made by India with Convention countries and which extend to, and are binding on, India on the date`
  line `of commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of the application of the Extradition Act, 1962 (34 of 1962) to offences under`
  line `this Act, any aircraft registered in a Convention country shall, at any time while that aircraft is in`
  line `service, be deemed to be within the jurisdiction of that country, whether or not it is for the time being`
  line `also within the jurisdiction of any other country.`
  line
  line `(3) None of the offences mentioned in section 3 shall be regarded, for the purposes of extradition`
  line `or mutual legal assistance, as a political offence or as an offence connected with a political offence or`
  line `as an offence inspired by political motives and a request for extradition or for mutual legal assistance`
  line `based on such an offence shall not be refused on the sole ground that it concerns a political offence or`
  line `an offence connected with a political offence or an offence inspired by political motives.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (28922)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Provision as to bail.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00011_201630_1517807328179&sectionId=28922&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00011_201630_1517807328179
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), no person accused of an offence punishable under this Act shall, if in`
  line `custody, be released on bail or on his own bond, unless,––`
  line
  line `(a) the Public Prosecutor has been given an opportunity to oppose the application for such`
  line `release; and`
  line
  line `(b) where Public Prosecutor opposes the application, the Designated Court is satisfied that`
  line `there are reasonable grounds for believing that he is not guilty of such offence and that he is not`
  line `likely to commit any offence while on bail.`
  line
  line `(2) The limitations on granting of bail as specified in sub-section (1) are in addition to the`
  line `limitation under the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), or any other law for the time`
  line `being in force, on granting bail.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing contained in this section shall be deemed to affect the special powers of the High`
  line `Court regarding bail under section 439 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (28923)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Contracting parties to Convention.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00011_201630_1517807328179&sectionId=28923&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00011_201630_1517807328179
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by notification, certify`
  line `as to who are the contracting parties to the Hague Convention and to what extent they have availed`
  line `themselves of the provisions of the Convention, and any such notification shall be conclusive`
  line `evidence of the matters certified therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (28924)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Power to treat certain aircraft to be registered in Convention countries.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00011_201630_1517807328179&sectionId=28924&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00011_201630_1517807328179
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the`
  line `Central Government is satisfied that the requirements of sub-section (2) have been satisfied in relation`
  line `to any aircraft, it may, by notification, direct that such aircraft shall, for the purposes of this Act, be`
  line `treated as registered in such Convention country as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Convention countries establish joint air transport operating organisations or`
  line `international operating agencies, which operate aircraft which are subject to joint or international`
  line `registration, shall, by appropriate means, designate for each aircraft, the country among them which`
  line `shall exercise the jurisdiction and have the attributes of the country of registry for the purposes of the`
  line `Convention and shall give notice thereof to the Secretary General of the International Civil Aviation`
  line `Organisation who shall communicate the notice to all Convention countries.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (28925)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Previous sanction necessary for prosecution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00011_201630_1517807328179&sectionId=28925&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00011_201630_1517807328179
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `No prosecution for an offence under this Act`
  line `shall be instituted except with the previous sanction of the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (28926)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Presumption as to offences under sections 3 and 5.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00011_201630_1517807328179&sectionId=28926&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00011_201630_1517807328179
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `In a prosecution for an offence under`
  line `section 3 or section 5, if it is proved that---`
  line
  line `(a) the arms, ammunitions or explosives were recovered from the possession of the accused`
  line `and there is reason to believe that such arms, ammunitions or explosives of similar nature were`
  line `used in the commission of such offence; or`
  line
  line `(b) there is evidence of use of force, threat of force or any other form of intimidation caused`
  line `to the crew or passengers in connection with the commission of such offence,`
  line
  line `the Designated Court shall presume, unless the contrary is proved, that the accused has committed such offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (28927)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00011_201630_1517807328179&sectionId=28927&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00011_201630_1517807328179
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding`
  line `shall lie against any person for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in`
  line `pursuance of the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against the Central Government for any damage`
  line `caused or likely to be caused for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in`
  line `pursuance of the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (28928)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Powers of investigating officers to seize or attach property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00011_201630_1517807328179&sectionId=28928&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00011_201630_1517807328179
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any officer,`
  line `referred to in section 6, while conducting an inquiry or investigation has a reason to believe that any`
  line `property, movable or immovable, or both, is relatable to the commission of the offence in relation to`
  line `which such inquiry or investigation is being conducted, is likely to be concealed, transferred or dealt`
  line `with in any manner which will result in disposal of such property, he may make an order for seizing`
  line `such property and where it is not practicable to seize such property, he may make an order of`
  line `attachment directing that such property shall not be transferred or otherwise dealt with, except with`
  line `the prior permission of the officer making such order, and a copy of such order shall be served on the`
  line `person concerned.`
  line
  line `(2) Any order made under sub-section (1) shall have no effect unless the said order is confirmed`
  line `by an order of the Designated Court, within a period of forty-eight hours of its being made.`
  line
  line `(3) The Designated Court may either confirm or revoke the order of seizure or attachment referred`
  line `to in sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding the confirmation of the order by the Designated Court under sub-section (3),`
  line `any person aggrieved by the order of attachment made under sub-section (1), may make an`
  line `application to the Designated Court for revocation of said order within a period of thirty days from the`
  line `date of confirmation of the order under sub-section (3).`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (28929)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Confiscation and forfeiture of property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00011_201630_1517807328179&sectionId=28929&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00011_201630_1517807328179
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `Where any order is made by the Designated`
  line `Court under section 4 for confiscation of movable or immovable property or both, of the accused,`
  line `then, such property shall stand forfeited to the Government free from all encumbrances:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Designated Court may, during the period of such trial, order that all or any of`
  line `the properties, movable or immovable, or both, belonging to the accused be attached, and in case such`
  line `trial ends in conviction, then, the property so attached shall stand forfeited to Government free from`
  line `all encumbrances.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (28930)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `General power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00011_201630_1517807328179&sectionId=28930&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00011_201630_1517807328179
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, make`
  line `rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every rule made under this Act by the Central Government shall be laid, as soon as may be`
  line `after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days`
  line `which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the`
  line `expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both`
  line `Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be`
  line `made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case`
  line `may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the`
  line `validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (28931)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Repeal and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00011_201630_1517807328179&sectionId=28931&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00011_201630_1517807328179
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Anti-Hijacking Act, 1982 (65 of 1982) is hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) The repeal of the said Act shall not affect––`
  line
  line `(a) the previous operation of, or anything duly done or suffered under, or any action taken or`
  line `purported to have been done or taken including any notification, order or notice made or issued,`
  line `or any appointment, confirmation or declaration made or any authorisation granted or any`
  line `document or instrument executed or any direction given, under the Act so repealed, shall, in so far`
  line `as it is not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, be deemed to have been done or taken`
  line `under the corresponding provisions of this Act; or`
  line
  line `(b) any right, privilege or obligation or liability acquired, accrued or incurred under the said`
  line `Act; or`
  line
  line `(c) any penalty, forfeiture or punishment incurred in respect of any offence under the said`
  line `Act; or`
  line
  line `(d) any investigation, legal proceeding or remedy in respect of any such right, privilege,`
  line `obligation, liability, penalty, forfeiture or punishment as aforesaid,`
  line
  line `and, any such investigation, legal proceeding or remedy may be instituted, continued or enforced and`
  line `any such penalty, forfeiture or punishment may be imposed as if the said Act had not been repealed.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
